  "prompt": "How do I know if a shy guy likes me?",
  "response": "Figuring out if a shy guy likes you can be a bit challenging because their behavior might not be as overt as someone who is more outgoing. However, there are several subtle signs you can look for to determine if a shy guy has feelings for you. Here are some indicators:\n\n### Body Language\n1. **Eye Contact**: Shy guys might avoid eye contact due to nervousness, but you might catch them stealing glances at you.\n2. **Smiling**: If he smiles when he sees you or when you're talking, it's a good sign that he enjoys your company.\n3. **Proximity**: He might try to be near you, but not too close. For instance, he might sit next to you or choose to stand close by in group settings.\n\n### Verbal Cues\n1. **Nervousness**: He might stammer, speak quietly, or seem a bit awkward when talking to you.\n2. **Compliments**: If he gives you genuine compliments, especially about non-physical traits, it could be a sign of interest.\n3. **Engagement**: He might ask you questions about your life, your interests, or your opinions, showing that he wants to get to know you better.\n\n### Behavior\n1. **Acts of Kindness**: He might do small things to help you out, like holding the door, offering to carry something for you, or helping you with a task.\n2. **Remembering Details**: If he remembers small details you've mentioned in past conversations, it indicates that he pays close attention to what you say.\n3. **Social Media Interaction**: He might like your posts or stories on social media more frequently than others.\n\n### Around Others\n1. **Behavior Change**: He might act differently around you compared to how he acts with others. He could be quieter or more nervous when you're around.\n2. **Friends' Hints**: Sometimes, his friends might drop hints or tease him when you're around, indicating that he's talked about you.\n\n### Digital Communication\n1. **Texting**: If he initiates texts or responds quickly and keeps the conversation going, it could be a sign of interest.\n2. **Emojis and Tone**: Pay attention to the use of emojis or the tone of his messages. Flirty or playful tones can indicate romantic interest.\n\n### Testing the Waters\nIf you're still unsure, you can try to initiate more interactions:\n1. **Start a Conversation**: See how he responds if you start talking to him. Does he seem happy to chat?\n2. **Spend Time Together**: Suggest doing something together, like grabbing a coffee or working on a project. His reaction can be telling.\n\nRemember, shy guys might need more encouragement to express their feelings openly. If you're interested in him, showing some interest back can help him feel more comfortable. Just be patient and take things at a pace that feels right for both of you.",
